headline: CNN Live Event/Special
subHeadline: East Coast And Central Time Ring In New Year 2024. Aired 12:30- 2:05a ET

utterances.speaker: SARA SIDNER, CNN CORRESPONDENT
utterances.sentences: The countdowns have begun. I am Sara Sidner, here with Cari Champion.

utterances.speaker: CARI CHAMPION, CORRESPONDENT, ESPN

utterances.sentences: Both of us.

utterances.speaker: NELLY
utterances.sentences: Yes, yes, yes. She's rocking out. ELAM

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: She's stunning, by the way.

utterances.speaker: NELLY
utterances.sentences: Thank you so much. But I mean, you know --

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: But the love is real.

utterances.speaker: NELLY
utterances.sentences: Yes, and we're very, very thankful for all the fans' support.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: I love that, I love that.So, Ashanti is here with us in spirit, you guys. And I'm going to try to be like Nelly and be all positive as we turn 50 this year. He just killed it onstage, you guys.

utterances.speaker: NELLY
utterances.sentences: Thank you so much.

utterances.sentences: We love Ashanti.Fitty. Fitty.

utterances.speaker: NELLY
utterances.sentences: We're all here.

And so it has been such a wonderful opportunity for me to sit with this lovely woman and just talk to her about our evening of fun.And I want to tell the viewers at home, because I'm sure that you all see this, but one of the things -- one of my new year's resolutions is to often tell people how amazing they are and give them their flowers. And you came on my show earlier this year. I hope we can show this photo.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: You are tricking me, now. Because you did this without me knowing.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: You said we don't ever not have a line, using a double negative.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: You know, we're pretty lucky.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: I have to say, we're lucky. Because we don't have to stand in that line.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: I see what's going on. You guys invited me so you didn't have to stand in line for brisket. I totally understand.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I mean -- I mean, that was the main reason. But Texas is known for its barbecue, so it only makes sense.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: Yes, yes.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Your story is really humble, and -- and I'm looking at someone who, as we talk about ideas. And the idea I got with you was just to keep trying, just figure it out. You always say, if you fail, it doesn't turn out, I'm going to figure it out again.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: Just keep going.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Just keep going. And so what has been the key to your success? Is that it?

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: Well, we use, a lot of salt. That's the main thing. A lot of -- a lot of time on fires.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.sentences: You are not vegan!

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN

utterances.speaker: SIDNER

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: It is OK, judge free zone in Texas.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I mean, goodness, it's so amazing. Honestly, what do you think is the difference? What separates you from everyone else?James Beard Award winner?

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: Yes, there's that. We cook everything, hopefully, as close to perfection as possible. That's about all I got.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: As much as you can do. All right. So, if folks want to get this, and I know you have your own sauce, you even have barbecue pits.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: We do.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You sell barbecue pits?

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: We do, we shall barbecue pits.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: How did you start doing that? FRANKLINpits out there for people.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: And so you cornered the market on that, as well?

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: We're some pretty hard-core do-it-yourself people.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: So, this is my goal in life and another new year's resolution. Let's just start making them.

utterances.sentences: You got a lot of them.

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Yes, exactly. Can we get that? Can we get that happening for us?

utterances.speaker: FRANKLIN
utterances.sentences: Let me make some calls.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK, thank you.

utterances.sentences: Well, Franklin's and chill. It's kind of like a term the kids are using these days.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Oh God. Did I just --

utterances.sentences: We are in the Central Time Zone. It's soi beautiful. It is 50 degrees. It feels so good. Sorry, New York. It feels so good here.

utterances.sentences: But it's just, like, a nice feel.

utterances.speaker: SANCHEZ
utterances.sentences: Sara -- Sara.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER

utterances.speaker: SANCHEZ
utterances.sentences: I was rusty. I was rusty. Look, I was rusty. I was rusty.Sara and Cari, it is such a pleasure to be with you. I haven't done that since I was 15 years old. You know the pride of Miami lives down the street from here. You grew up there, Sara, Phil. Hey, listen, I wanted to share something special with you guys. And first off, I have to say, I have to say, I'm really sorry if this offends any of our vegan and vegetarian friends, but this is part of our culture, our Latin tradition. I have my friend Renee here from Ball and Chain, world-famous bar in Miami, to explain why, on very significant holidays, Cubans, Venezuelans, Puerto Ricans, people from all sorts of places in Latin America, they did a hole in the ground, and they roast a pig in a cahachina (ph). We have one right here. Renee, what does this mean to you as a Cuban American?

utterances.speaker: RENEE
utterances.sentences: Well, here at ball and chain we love to celebrate the Cuban culture. And this is the epitome of Cuban culture, a lutron (ph), on Nochebuena on New Year's Eve, maybe even on Thanksgiving.Look at that right there. So, us Cubans, we look forward to that one day of the year. Right? In Cuba, it's not every day you can eat this, but rather the family you bring everyone from the neighborhood and you get together and you eat and you feast on a delicious lutron (Ph). And here we are at the famous Ball and Chain with the best lutron (ph) in town.

utterances.speaker: SANCHEZ
utterances.sentences: It is truly a special thing. You bring the neighborhood together, that sense of community, that sense of belonging. And we're about to break pork.

utterances.speaker: RENEE
utterances.sentences: We're about to break pork.

utterances.speaker: SANCHEZ
utterances.sentences: What do you think? Can we try it?

utterances.speaker: RENEE
utterances.sentences: Let's do it, the Cuban way. (SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

utterances.speaker: SANCHEZ
utterances.sentences: I will toss it back to you, Sara and Cari, thank you so much. I'll save some for you if you want.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: That looks so good.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Please do.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Please tell you and your friend, (SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE).

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Buena nueva.All right, guys. Now we are joined by actor and "Dancing with the Stars" winner, got to be specific, season 13, not the laters but the earliers. The earliers.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: J.R. Martinez.J.R. MARTINEZ, SEASON 13 WINNER OF "DANCING WITH THE STARS": What's up, ladies? Welcome to Austin.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year from the East.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: Happy new year. Thanks for having me. How are you guys liking Austin?

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: We love Austin.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: It's great, right? And I didn't know you speak Spanish.(CROSSTALK)

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: I grew up in Miami, Boris grew up in Miami, so --

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: You got Spanglish.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Yes. Yes.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Same, I grew up in L.A., so Spanglish here.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: People at home know Spanglish, too.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: We know the Spanglish.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: We can make this work. But you're going to be here with me.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: You have an incredible, incredible story. You've been through it.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Can you give us a little sense of kind of what you went through and how you came out the other side? And now you're inspiring people with your motivational speaking. Like, people come to try and get a clue as to how to get out of their own stuff, I will say.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: The first thing is, you got to go through it. You've got to go through it. You've got to lean in.So many of us spend so much time -- and I did, too -- early in my recovery, just trying to avoid it, just trying to run away from it. Because it felt too uncomfortable for me to do it, and address it. And finally, when I learned to, like, lean into it and understand that I had every capability to actually go through it, I came out on the other side with so many lessons and so many gifts and so many valuable things that I could pass onto other people. But listen, I was in the military. I was 19 years old when I was injured overseas in Iraq. You know, I spent more time on "Dancing with the Stars" that I did on active duty in the military. My military career was cut very short, and I spent three years in a hospital about 70 miles down the road, recovering in San Antonio, Texas.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Three years?

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: Three years.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I was going to say, can you give us just -- I know it's television, but give us a little summary of what happened to you, for folks that aren't familiar.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: So, I was driving a Humvee through a city called Karbala in Iraq, and the front left tire of the Humvee that I was driving ran over a roadside bomb.And I was trapped inside of the Humvee, and I was engulfed in flames. You can look at me on camera. You can understand that I sustained some burns throughout my body. But, you know, for so many years after my injury, my identity was purely a burn victim. That's what I said. I was a burn victim. That's what people told me. You're a disabled veteran. And I just embraced that. I just, like, that's what I am. And when I became part of the burn community, I realized that I'm not a victim. I'm a burn survivor. And I'm not a disabled veteran. I'm a veteran. And I'm not somebody that has a disability. I'm somebody that -- this disses the "dis" in disability and proves to the world that I got nothing but ability. And honestly, "Dancing with the Stars" was my opportunity to show the world that I'm so much more than what they see on the surface. It give people a chance to get inside into J.R.'s personality. And I'm a clown, and I'm joking around.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: And now you're an actor, too.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You're an actor, too.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Taking things to the next level.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You went from "Dancing with the Stars" to being a main character on "All My Children."

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: No acting experience.

utterances.speaker: MARTIENZ
utterances.sentences: Here's the crazy thing -- here's, like so people -- listen, it's New Year's. Everyone is doing vision boards. Everyone is talking about goals for '24 and all this stuff, spending $5,000 on magazines just so they can cut them up. Stick them to a board, whatever. I get it. Whatever you got to do, if it works.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You're speaking to me.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: So let me tell you this quick story. So about three months after I was injured, I was in the hospital recovering and my mom (SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE). And I used to watch novellas with my mom every night in the hospital.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: The drama is so good.

utterances.speaker: MARTINEZ
utterances.sentences: It was so good, you don't even got it to speak Spanish to know what's going on.
